comments.text:
What does fraternal twins mean
﻿
comments.author: Franki Marshall

comments.text:
Fraternal is when twins look nothing alike. An example could be twins that 
are a boy and a girl, they would obviously be fraternal because they don't 
look alike. You could possibly tell that they are siblings, but not twins.
Identical is when twins look almost exactly the same. For example, Brooklyn 
and Bailey are identical. In this case, you would be able to tell that they 
are twins. I hope this helped!
